  "prompt": "How can I prepare for CAT 2017?",
  "response": "To prepare for CAT 2017, here are some comprehensive steps:\n\n1. Understand the Exam Pattern\n- Three sections: Verbal Ability & Reading Comprehension, Data Interpretation & Logical Reasoning, Quantitative Ability\n- Total duration: 180 minutes\n- No negative marking for non-MCQ questions\n\n2. Study Material\n- Standard CAT preparation books\n- Previous years' question papers\n- Mock test series\n- Online study resources\n\n3. Subject-wise Preparation\n- Verbal Ability:\n  \u2022 Reading comprehension\n  \u2022 Grammar\n  \u2022 Vocabulary\n  \u2022 Para jumbles\n\n- Quantitative Ability:\n  \u2022 Arithmetic\n  \u2022 Algebra\n  \u2022 Geometry\n  \u2022 Data interpretation\n\n- Logical Reasoning:\n  \u2022 Puzzles\n  \u2022 Seating arrangements\n  \u2022 Data sufficiency\n  \u2022 Logical sequences\n\n4. Preparation Strategy\n- Create a study schedule\n- Practice mock tests regularly\n- Analyze your performance\n- Focus on weak areas\n- Time management\n\n5. Recommended Resources\n- Books by Arun Sharma\n- TIME/IMS mock tests\n- Career Launcher study material\n- Online platforms like Testbook, Gradeup\n\n6. Additional Tips\n- Regular practice\n- Stay updated with current affairs\n- Improve reading speed\n- Work on time management skills",
